tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: All measured parameters are within normal limits for this 85-year-old female patient. Glycemic control, renal function, electrolytes, and lipid profile are unremarkable. No laboratory evidence of acute or chronic metabolic, renal, or lipid abnormalities at this time. Continued routine monitoring is recommended.
